featured_reviews.review_text:
Bought the "Spicy Beef Korean Rice" or something at $16.39 in total, recommended by presumably the owner.

Was expecting the beef to be at least beef slices, but turned out to be a thin layer of minced meat in sauce.

Just sauced minced meat, kimchi, seaweed, pickles, and mostly rice in the standard sized takeaway container. Not even an egg. Beware.

Food here is very good. All dishes are very well presented and their ingredients are all imported directly from Korea. I will definitely recommend the spicy seafood kimchi carbonara the most because the taste is perfect for me. It’s not too salty or creamy. The texture of the noodles is perfect as well. The Laoban is a very genuine guy and has very good customer service. Atmosphere is also fantastic. The cold noodles took a little longer to be served but it’s because they have their own way of making the noodles taste good by placing it in a machine before it’s served so no complaints.
Tasty food and friendly service. Strongly recommend the Spicy Kimchi Carbonara. Really nice and delicious. Will definitely come again!

Very disappointed with the food and service.  The price for "buy 2 free 2 meat" BBQ was shown at around $26 on the menu, but it turns out to be $69 after adding to cart. The e-menu was really hard to navigate.

The portion of the food was little and was told we cant top up the side dishes except for the lettuce. Even so, the lettuce was served in a small bowl and in odd shapes which made it difficult to wrap the meat. All the other korean restaurants i went to served unlimited side dishes.

The kimchi soup, placed in the middle of the bbq pot, was priced at $7.90 with just kimchi in it. No laden was given, though it's quite obvious we will need one. The restaurant is very short-handed.

The only thing good about this place is the they serve decent beer, and outdoor dining is romantic. If you are looking to have a decent korean meal, you should go elsewhere. But if you are looking for a nice place to chill, then you can consider coming here.

Enjoyed a whole new outdoor alfresco dining experience at Seoul Good with delectable & affordable Korean cuisine from $9.90+ at Punggol East Container Park. Conveniently located within walking distance from Riviera LRT, they have Korean BBQ, fried chicken, ramen, bulgogi and many more, even fine selection of beer on tap and cocktails.

We had:
🥢Mul-Naengmyeon Cold Noodle $15.90+: Forget about hot and humid weather with this refreshing & appetizing noodle served in icy cold broth. Using noodles imported from Korea, the noodles had an enjoyable qq and chewy texture. The accompanied seaweed, sliced cucumbers, Korean pears, boiled egg and kimchi further elevated the overall taste! Special mention to the kimchi which was so so so crunchy!
🥢Spicy Seafood Kimchi Carbonara $17.90+: Pasta was al dente and was a perfect match with their inhouse made spicy kimchi sauce which was creamy, flavourful and not heavy. We also enjoyed the variety of fresh seafood. Unique pasta that you cannot miss!
🥢Kabi Pork Belly $15.90+: Authentic marination and pork belly was flavourful, tender and juicy.
🥢Special Flaming Scallop $21.90+: Watch the crew torched the scallop into flames! The savoury special sauce was delicious and scallops were fresh!

Great ambience & vibes with great service from friendly crew. The portions were also generous. I saw many happy diners with their Korean BBQ and fried chicken which looked so mouthwatering. Definitely need to try these next round.

Neat little place to have dinner. Alfresco dining atmosphere.

Taste wise, nothing fantastic but was not too bad either. Price was quite high for a place like this. Service was okay, boss was friendly.  Parking was rather easy too.

Unless you live around this area of Punggol, coming here can be a chore due to its distance. Otherwise, a nice place to dine and relax.

Don't order the jajangmyeon, it's below av. Naeng myeon is nice with lots of Kimchi. The hot and spicy chicken wings was really spicy but it's good and crispy. Mud pie is on the small side. The banana ice cream is nice, not too sweet

Tried it out after seeing some reviews. Quite disappointed in the place, not even close to an authentic Korean place.

Ordered 3 for 3 ($75+), 2 for 2 ($50+), Naengmyeon, Jjangmyeon, and other side dishes. Total amounted to $350 for 10 pax. Interesting idea to have a "Buy 3 Free 3" BBQ dishes when it's not really "Free" since 2.5 plates of meat is just nice for 1 pax.

Complimentary side dishes are only given with each BBQ set (2 for 2 OR 3 for 3) and are Not free flow, given 2 saucer sized sets for 10 Pax.

Meat was fresh and of good cuts but portion is little. Would recommend the Naengmyeon, Spicy Bulgogi. Chicken wings are not marinated well.
Overall the meal feels healthy due to lack of salts in the food.

Staff were very quick in attending to us due to lack of patrons.

Love the location, many other restaurants around in the area. To be warned that this place is 80% open air and though sheltered, rain may still affect your experience.

Bad BBQ experience - overpriced and fake discount. $26 for 5 small pieces of meat, less than 100g. Cold noodles is also a mess. Will not come again.
Very good food and atmosphere, I recommend the fish & chips Food
Great Spicy Beef Bulgogi

Additionally, a small fire led to slow cooking, and when we mentioned it to the owner, the response was perplexing, suggesting adding more would somehow speed up the process. They were very reluctant to do refunds for us too.  Overall, the visit left us dissatisfied.

Very very nice experience!

We had an amazing dinner at Seoul Good in Punggol Container Park last Thursday! The restaurants beautiful alfresco dining provided the perfect ambiance for a delightful evening. The highlight of the meal was definitely the Sweet & Spicy Chicken Wings, priced at S$11.50. To add an extra touch of excitement, I couldnt resist trying the Flaming Cheese (S$7.90) that was set on fire right before my eyes. The combination of flavors was absolutely mouthwatering. For a unique treat, I indulged in the Special Flaming Scallop (S$14.90), which arrived with a tantalizing blend of sweet and savory sauces. It was truly an eye-opener! To beat the Singapore heat, I opted for the refreshing Naengmyeon Cold Noodles (S$15.90), a perfect choice for the warm weather. The Spicy Seafood Kimchi Carbonara (S$18.90) brought together the best of both worlds spice and creaminess for a delightful fusion dish. Lastly, I enjoyed a refreshing Ice Tea and Citron Tea to complement the flavors of the meal.
Lovely place with good food and atmosphere.

love this place! very nice place to chill and boss is very friendly haha always making small talks and engaging customers. My fave hangout

TERRIBLE EXPERIENCE!! We had to wait for 1hour for our food to arrive. There was practically no service! When the army stew arrived, what we got is SO TOTALLY different from what was shown in the menu!! It s so not worth the $55 charged for the food! The ingredients were just spam, sausage, fried popcorn chicken, toboki, veggies, tofu and some dumplings! We feel so cheated!! After the army stew, it took another 15 mins for our ordered rice bowl to arrive. We then reminded them that we still have fish and chips and white rice not served. Nobody came back to us about it. N we waited another 15-20 mins and had finished the rest of the meals by then My kid was starving and so I asked again and only after I said that we want to cancel the order were we informed that the order was being cooked and will be served shortly. I told them that was not our problem and we want to cancel and get a refund. They came back with $12 when the cost on the menu is $12.90 before gst and service charge!! They also didn t refund us for the white rice until we reminded them! Everything is just so terrible! We left home for dinner early so we didn t have to squeeze with the crowd but in the end had to wait for 1hr for our food to be served. Please do not go! We will not be coming back again! Definitely not worth the money and spoilt our dinner and mood!

Very disappointing dining experience . 1) 60 min wait for food & drinks . Just don t get it why is it so difficult to serve the drinks first ? We were prepared for the long wait for food . But just to grab 2 bottles of beer off the fridge and homemade pre-prepared drinks takes  60 min ?? 2) Korean BBQ - worst ever . Marinated Beef was virtually minced that it s so hard to cook that it fell off from the holes on the grill . On the other hand No scissors / thongs were provided to cut the slab of pork . Seafood ( frozen dory fish , 2 pcs of squid ring , 1 scallop and clams ) are just taken off the freezer . Korean water soup - just plain water ? 3) space was so limited on the table that the servers just passed the food to our hands to fix the problem on our own . No sorry / apologies.

food was damn sad for its price ($30 in total in this review) and did not uphold level ground t&cs (no discount given) as shown on its website. Edit: extremely sad for the price. I had paid $15 per meal in order to bite into 3 pieces of seashell in my aglio olio + the food had virtually no seasoning. Batter on fish fritter was hard and firm like a piece of wet roti prata, and the fish had a structural integrity similar to firm tau kua. Aglio olio had a tinge of mee sedap flavour. The most flavourful thing on the plate are the fries, baked beans and the slice of lemon.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hi Ze, weekend no usage of level ground as T&C has already giving to management 2 years ago. Please check. As for the food thanks for the feedback, we will check on it as this is the first time we got this product feedback. Once again thanks a lot if you want to use level ground card please take note on the timing accordingly. Next time u come on weekday, food will be good and with levelground discount giving to u.

detailed_reviews.review_text: Neat little place to have dinner. Alfresco dining atmosphere. Taste wise, nothing fantastic but was not too bad either. Price was quite high for a place like this. Otherwise, a nice place to dine and relax.

Didn t expect much from this restaurant when I choose to dine in. But the result turned out to be amazing. I had tried so many sweet and spicy chicken in different country this their sweet & spicy chicken is really worth trying. Their other dish   Chicken Jjiaajangmyeon is really like wht they said taste good when it s hot. Not salty yet u can still taste the bery nice black bean flavour. Boss or the chef there is very friendly . He s humble, funny, approachable n really walk from table to table to ask for review n share his experience. Overall experience in this restaurant is excellent. Will rate this restaurant 8/10!!!!

First time trying and it didn t disappointment us at all! 4 of us and we ordered their chicken army stew and the special sauce chicken wings and totally satisfied! The service was great and quite personalised in fact! Will come back again and try other stuff! Too bad they aren t serving Bingsu at the moment, but the coke floats totally won the kids over.
Overall tasty food and nice ambience to chill out. But bring over insect repellent to prevent mosquito s bite.

Staff was very friendly, helpful and cheerful! Customer service was on the point. Food was above average and portion was good. Vibe was good too. Definitely recommend to come here if keen on Korean food or beer
Very good service and nice ambience!
Alfresco dining with a good cause

Came for dinner, the ginseng chicken soup is tasty but what a sad piece of chicken leg, looks like a sad dish honestly for 17 bucks. I had the seafood kimchi carbonara, the mussel shells were broken and I bit into it drinking the sauce wth!? Pls stop this kind of shell seafood in cream sauce, cant see the shell withe seaweed flakes. Very disappointing experience.

Excellent service also very good food. Ordered The Fried Chicken Cutlet With Rice And It was crispy and juicy and hot. The Coke Float was cold and refreshing tolc cool it down. Def worth coming all the way here. Would come again.
The boss is very friendly and entertain anyone that is there

Kimchi soup is ok probably something you can get out of kimchi soup instant noodle and add some ingredients. Sweet and spicy chicken wing is lacklustre slight hint of sweet with next to no spiciness, if you are looking for something authentic look elsewhere but if you look for a decent chicken wing, it is there. Lastly the cold noodle is horrible, very bland and not at all authentic. Too much corner cut for that. The homemade tea is a good mix of sweetness and sourness although on the pricy side. Despite what the owner reply is they do allow smokers, throughout my whole dinner session the nearby table keep lighting up.
The food is disappointed.chicken is not crunchy and the taste not nice.is not recommended.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Sorry may i know what happen? Out recommending to eat the chicken when is hot. As our chicken is juicy

detailed_reviews.review_text: Got aircon v good and chicken wingsyyds

The food is normal and expensive.. nothing outstanding. The drinks got messed up even when s not crowded. If you are looking for a nice environment still ok. But if you are looking for nice korea food then definitely is not here.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hi Mr Ho, May we know what happen?

detailed_reviews.review_text: Food was good, service was excellent   We had two stews, chicken wings, and some sides (forgot to photos of the stews and wings)

Level Ground members, expect to be disappointed. Other than the fact that the beer isn t redeemable on weekends, the 15% doesn t apply to all the food. Food was OK only- the only friendly staff has also left the company  Regret bringing my friend here to celebrate her birthday. P/S: I paid for the beer on my own in my photos.
I m a level ground member and was extremely disappointed to learn that members do not get any benefit during week-ends. Other branches are much more accommodating for their members.
Very good service and the staff guy is very nice   Dog friendly and service is really good    They offer water for your dog. My dog like the fried Korean chicken.
The boss is kind!
Good service, friendly host. Helped with deciding what to order. So we have 5pax ordered one seafood army stew and fried chicken. Add-on order fries to go with beer.

The kimchi chicken spaghetti is like a must when one dines here. Service is very good and all applause goes to Milton who made our visit here even better with his awesome service! Oh! The coffee here is also nice if you want to chill spirit free! Haha!
Awesome food... Great service
Great food, nice ambience and friendly staff. Feels at home.
Great food, drinks and customer service!
Awesome food and drinks! Will come back again
Food quality is good and service staff is friendly.

Comfy and cozy! Friendly staffs and food portion is good too! The hot and spicy fried chicken is really spicy and the kimchi soup with rice is very flavourful! Perfect food to eat during a rainy day. Must try   .
Service was excellent and food is tasty! Ill recommend the hot and spicy fried chicken!

Dined in (Punggol East) on Saturday during peak dinner time. Ordered some chicken wings, Korean rabboki, and grilled chicken chop with chips. Waited 30 minutes for our food to come. Grilled chicken chop and chips was not hot, the side of beans was cold. The popcorn chicken in the rabboki was also not hot. Aside from temperature flavours were nothing special, overall very mediocre food, not worth the price or time. Seoul good, so bad.

Great food, nice ambience and really friendly staff! Here for the first time and was impressed with Elvin s hospitality. The alcohol here is slightly pricey but the beef bulgogi is definitely worth a try!
Fun fair near it
Naengmyun wasnt that good, food was just average tbh, dont expect alot
Good food & funny guy that works here!
Cold noodle, spicy fish cake soup. My favourite. Everything also very good.
Staffs are very friendly. The foods are very nice and comfortable environment.
The staffs are very friendly and attentive. They are very fun loving people! Food was served quite fast and good. Nachos is good too.
Very good service!
Service very good food is great

Very great customer service, tried the new dish, dory burger. Very interesting concept   rly amazing customer service, went in the hot afternoon with pet dog and was still comfortably siting in the open.
Great food and service! Would come back again :) But the portions are quite filling!
Nice environment. Very friendly and nice staff with good food and portions! Would recommend for a chill time
The food and service was great!! The portions were also very substantial. I especially love the spicy beef rice and fries! Would definitely come back again.
Good food, nice environment!

Went on a Friday evening and it did not look so crowded yet we had to wait 45 mins for the army stew. The only thing good is that the ingredients were generous but the soup base was underwhelming. It was not bad, but did not leave me wanting more. We were supposed to collect our own food but the calling system was confusing. The receipt show an order number but the food was called based on table number. We saw some tables missed their calls too. I would have given 2 stars if not for the friendly staff who was apologetic when we missed our call and waited 30mins for our drinks. Anyway, they need to improve the system and the soup for army stew.
Went in during the busy period.  Food is good.  Feel that they lack of manpower feel quite chaos
The Korean Special chicken wings are superb! Will definitely come back for more!
Very good food and ambience
Good food , friendly staff and nice servings
Service is very good and I like the beer which was served. Will definitely go again
has a very nice scenic view, great place for a date but food wise is okay(im not a foodie, i just enjoy company )
Food and ambiance is good, staff is very hospitable as well. Came here for some bingsu but its no longer in the menu.
Nice place to chill and grab dinner. Cozy atmosphere and friendly staff
good service and friendly staffs
Food is nice, service is good. Definitely coming back again!
The service is absolutely incredible The waiters are friendly and nice. Every time I come here, I get good reviews
Good food, nice place
Great ambience and great service by Alvin!
food was good. nice place for small grp gatherings :D
The staff were very friendly and food was okay :-) will come back for the beer :-D ambience was good indoors
Nice beer and nice service!:D
come find shuai ge elvin :))
Nice restraunt and good ambience. Nice food and drinks, a must for good Korean food.
Very good food and very good service
the waiter was so kind and nice , the food is so delicious
very cool waiter and food damn nice
Ginseng chicken soup was flavourful! Chicken rappoki is worth a try!
The fried rice was very fragrant and nicely seasoned. Chicken was well grilled and the ginseng chicken soup was flavourful. A very satisfying meal for a wet and cool evening

We went on Wed night right after our dinner. Ordered wings, fried enoki and soju. Reasonable price as well. Thumbs up. Staffs were very friendly. Most importantly there s aircon area. Will definitely return back to try other food.
Service overall good. Food was decent and their beer requires acquired taste.

Love the vibes of this place, it is our go to korean place to satisfy our k cravings. Fried chicken, ginseng chic, lemon tea are our usual order. Wasnt in time to take a decent picture of the wings as they sweeped off the plate soon after it was served Service is tops, with staff frequently checking in and offering more sauces. Do check out this gem!
Great food and chill drinking.
Good place will come again
great sugar mommy
Super cup of roof beer float, the service staff is very nice, praise! !
Salmon was nicely done! Anyways the staff here is super friendly so kudos to you!
Tried their mul naeng myun, taste is decent but portion is really big! Value for money :-)
Ambient environment, with relaxing music from the next door... Beers are cheap, 10btls at 55bucks nett! Enjoyed my date time with my husband during our day off!
Yummy naengmyun and jjajangmyeon and chicken cutlet rice, staff are so friendly, love the vibes!

Staff, Alvin was very attentive and kind esp since we had a baby in tow. Wait for food was not long (ard 15mins) considering it was a public holiday. Loved the rice bowls! Will visit again. Super thumbs up to Alvin once again!

This place must NOT go. We waited more than a hour at this place and they mixed up our orders but we just ate it as we were so hungry and sick of tired of waiting. Very disorganised and the food is awful. Ordered the sweet and spicy wings but the sauce has 0 flavour and the soup was so bland. The beef rice was just beef thrown over rice. So bad. Everyone around us was super unhappy as well - extremely bad experience. Dont bother.

Seoul Good (Punggol East) - Nice environment but it can be very crowded in the night and the place was filled with mosquitoes. There were too many smokers around as it is alfresco dining and they can practically smoke anywhere. As you can imagine, they can even smoke while having the meal at their table. And yes, the tables around me. Oh gosh! So, something to take note if you decide to wind and chill here. As for the food, Korean flavoured with decent portion. Staffs were friendly, mainly from Malaysia and Taiwan. Majority of the staffs are Mandarin speaking
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hi Cassandra, customer are not allow to smoke in the premise during opening hour. We will look into it on this matter Thanks for ur feedback. Anyway most of us are singaporean.

detailed_reviews.review_text: Tried 2 of their crafted beers and kaarage chicken (comes with 3 sauces pairing). Not bad, beer were smooth and unique. Outdoor seating overlook the park connector

Headed over at night for a meal & was warmly served by 2 male service crew, ordered 3-Flavour Fried Chicken, Kimchi Soup & Spicy Beef Ricebowl & they tasted great! The fried chicken was crispy despite being drenched in the delicious sauce, kimchi soup was very flavourful & beef bowl was fragrant! To the 2 male service crew, thanks for hospitality
Food is really seoul good! Chef was really funny and nice too :)
I love the seafood creamy soup. Fried chicken were cripsy and tasty!
Nice food, great environment and great service    would recommend
Dinner become supper! Waited for so long for the dinner and staff are not attentive, hotpot boiling out still stand there and look at me!   Food rating 2 stars..
I was surprised by the quality of food and beverage. Service experience was very pleasant. Great place to chill.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks for your feedback we hope to see u again

detailed_reviews.review_text: Non smokers should not dine here! Horrible attitude of wait staff. They have no smoking signs clearly on the pillars by the outdoor seats. So this guy was just standing by the stable 100cm outside of the table smoking like a chimney. All the smoke was getting to us. We told the wait staff but he simply ignored us. We lost appetite, couldn t finish our food and just left. Please remove your no smoking signs if they are only there for show.
Good place to chill, boss is friendly and beer price has not raise. Cheaper than other place.
Food is good. Ambience is amazing. Strongly recommend!!!
A great place to just hang out with friends :) Friendly boss, great atmosphere.
solid place, gotta come

Food was soso, ordered seaweed tofu soup and its sweet?? And the army stew was just normal, soso only. Utensils were oily also. Had to swipe down everything before using. Worse thing was the boss (i think?) was smoking right outside a restaurant without a care of the customers. You think we want to smell your second hand smoke while eating hello??? And when asked to walk away, he shifted aside without apologising and even said that area is ok for smoking. Smokers should be banned in Singapore.
Food is ok BUT waiters did not enforce no smoking rule in the premise. When we approached a waiter to advise the smoker, the waiter just walked off and ignored us!
Still one of my fav spot for chill nights. Good food, good service and great chicken!!! Must visit place. Been coming here even before covid period. Such a treasure found.
Excellent service. Poor waiting time. Cannot trust the menu. It picture with a drink but when it came, the person says it doesnt comes with the drink.

Best part about dining in Seoul Good is the warm and friendly customer service : ) Other than having the simple kimchi soup, we also got the kimchi fried rice that came in a very big portion. Just slightly oily but fried chicken with the fried rice was great !!
Good experience. Food is fairly well priced. Ambience is good. Overall food is tasty.
Excellent service and reasonable price. Most impt kids and pet friendly hangout place. Will definitely patronise again!
the service was not good. it is unfortunate when businesses do not train their staff to have a customer service mindset.

Its always nice to dine here and i especially love the vibes. Alfresco dining with great music and a really lively environment.   their tteokbokki and Korean wings . Always a must order when having Korean food.   #msgreedysis #greedybuddiez
Best kimchi fried rice I ve eaten! Food at the restaurant taste really good and service by the boss is superb too!
Great good, good Alfresco ambience, more importantly .excellent service! Staff are all very accommodating and friendly, even though there s no service charge!
Great food, nice casual ambience and most importantly, excellent service from the staff. Always a go-to pit stop for my cycling trips and casual family dinners.
food was only ok and long waiting time ... won t come back

Taking 20 orders at once and figuring out how to deal with them later on is not a proper way of managing a kitchen. We waited 50 minutes for a simple order and we only received it after complaining. Their soju is overpriced. Food was just alright. All staff is lost and stressed, minimise your orders / improve organization.

Went to the place to have a bing su but the machine was down for maintenance. Hope they fix up the machine soon. On the good note, the staff was really friendly and super service oriented. Rather satisfied with my chicken chop order too
Good

The food tastes good, and the service attitude is also OK~ It is recommended to go there in the afternoon as it is not noisy and does not have to wait too long   Come on, the food tastes good, and the service is also no bad.

detailed_reviews.review_text: The food was really tasty. All the dishes I order were presented and tasted amazing def gonna visit again

Came here last saturday & realise the queue was long , so i went to the cashier to make my order instead . The cashier lady ( Chloe ) was super polite and friendly. Despite the peak hours , she still did her service really well and even recommended me food       its super rare to see teenagers her age to give such a good service. 10/10 for her service . The food was good & most importantly kids friendly too 8/10 for the food & atmosphere !!
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hi Annabella,  thanks for your feedback.  We hope to see u again soon

detailed_reviews.review_text: Brilliant service. Super warm friendly to all customers, and even non-customers. From a short chat with the staff, noted that the ingredients were delicately curated and recipe was delicately designed. Kudos to the team.

detailed_reviews.review_text: Been here quite a few times and the food is always amazing. Always tasty and piping hot, fresh from the kitchen. Staff are friendly and accommodating, always happy to speak with you and checking if the food is alright. Occasionally they will suggest what to try and has so far never disappointed. A very nice place to have a meal with friends and family!
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hi Scott,  thanks for the feedback hope to see u again

detailed_reviews.review_text: The food is good and the staffs provide excellent service! Especially the boss is very helpful and friendly. I strongly recommend to patronize the restaurant and will definitely come again!

Elvin Pang is excellent and fantastic service for us as customer. The food are nice and tasty. Good job and definitely will recommend to friends and come again Kimchi chicken spaghetti is highly recommended

The staff was polite and cooperative. They really need to improve their operational system.

The boss is also a very friendly chap. He came and chat with us and also told us he dont encourage us take away food. Eat there for the better taste. Not advisable to call grab food also because quality of food will change. Very comfortable open air experience when eating food. Great place to chill if you are in punggol. UNCLE RINGO Is there now! The kids can enjoy themselves with our childhood fav  uncle Ringo. Too bad no pasar malam... Else can buy sausage and walk around. Haha. I miss pasar malam!

We are checking on the system as no let us know your number we will feedback to the Resturant and also what your ordering. We welcome your feedback so that we are able to improve the serivce.

Number are called not in order n the only cons was the dishes doesnt serve all in one go but on the other hand, we get to savour our food individually instead of chomping down everything. detailed_reviews.review_text: Good ambience, good service and good food. This is my 2nd time visit this restaurant. I can say that the food now is much much better than I had before and there are more choices on the menu now. Definitely worth going again and try the other food on the menu.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks a lot sir how u enjoy our food. We hope to see u again

The cheese fries was good too. Overall the food was 4/5. But their service staff were really friendly and helpful and nice. So 5/5 for the overall. Would definitely recommend you dropping by to grab some korean food if you are ard punggol.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you we hope to see u again soon

detailed_reviews.review_text: The kimchi was very good though water-soaked. Enoki was oily which was a pity. Chicken wings were flavorful but lacks the crunch. Surprisingly the star was the nacho with beef which was flavorful and right textures. They have a beer promotion - 10 bottles for $55, before 8pm. Interesting beers with a choice of calamansi or mango with passion fruit syrup to be added into it. Self ordering via one of the kiosks. Service is friendly.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much as we are using fresh chicken directly from chill to cook. That is why the meat of the chicken is juicy. Hope u come back soon.  Thanks

detailed_reviews.review_text: Ride from Coney Island and had dinner here. V worth for the quality of food, chicken wing is a must to order ! We had beer, jiajiang noodle and fish n pasta , too bad no more bingsu but will definitely go back for the wings again! Staff v friendly , Service is excellent! *Kids friendly have aircon and baby chair
The ice tea is nice, special chicken wings lack the flavour and cheese fries taste abit weird with the additional sesames.

Food was so good. Especially their seaweed soup and teobokki. We bought cheese fries and popcorn chicken. Their french fries was good while popcorn chicken was underwhelming. But will definately visit again for their soup
Food was ok and love the lemon tea
Huge portion of food for the price paid. Nice place to hang. The uncle staff is friendly and attentive.
Serving is very huge... Cheese fries
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you, we hope you will introduce more friend to come.

detailed_reviews.review_text: All yummy but the tofu soup seems abit overpriced. Definitely go back for the fried chicken!
Love the spicy beef fries. Affordable with no gst and service charge. Boss is very friendly too.

Nice ambience and good value food for a night out. Had the rice bowls and the chicken wings. Go for the rice bowl and beer combo promo to get the best value! Will be back for sure. Just need to check the weather before going.
Nice food interesting place to chill.
highly recommand the sweet and spicy chicken wing. Taste the best
Very happy with the food & service! Keep up the good work!
Seafood Kimchi Carbonara

A good place for a nice korean food and soju. My family simply love their food especially the army srew and the fried chicken. I would highly recommend these two dishes. This is also a good place if you intend to chill out with family or friends. Can choose to be seated either indoor or outdoor. Personally I would recommend outdoor seating for 2 reasons : The indoor aircon is freezing cold. Not that comfortable if you intend to sit long. Their indoor seating is pretty small and quiet. Even if you will to talk softly, the echo of your sound can easily be heard in the whole room. Sometimes you may feel uncomfortable if other table patrons are chatting loudly. Excellent service. Good vibes overall !

Great vibes. But more importantly, the boss is very friendly. The boss do check with customers hows everything, and when we mentioned the hot chocolate is too thin, he immediately suggested to replace with new ones for us. Will come back again and highly recommend to come with friends
Family night out@!
Very nice korean food. Can choose to be seated indoors or outdoors.
Nice Korean food & beer at great prices. They also have western food menu. Mostly open space seating so not advisable to go during heavy rain or day time when the sun is high.
Normal price,normal taste,good atmosphere
Went for a quick bite after some coffee meeting nearby. Affordable Korean food and sorta cosy.
Great food n ambience
The fish and chip is really bad the rest is ok
Nice place to hang and chill. The Korean beef bulgogi I had was really tasty. The server was very friendly, and gave good recommendations on what to order.

Food was average but very friendly and helpful staff. The ambience was also nice for a chill out at the end of a work day. Could see they have many regulars, meaning this place has left a gd impression for many, including me.
Excellent service! Went on a Saturday night and it was crowded and busy but they still tried to accommodate our 7 pax by moving tables around just for us. Really great food too!
Soo good

Good vibes overall!! Outdoor seating was vast but due to the downpour we opted for indoor seats. Do note that there s only 3-4 tables indoors. Ordered the spicy bulgogi chicken - really juicy and savoury   Salted fries were delicious too! Loved the peach soju!! Price was relatively affordable :)

not that fantastic. rice was hard. if already serve with ceramic plate shld just use steel fork and spoon, not compatible. ordered the chicken kimchi carbonara but barely any chicken bites, not worth it. the duck rice bowl was good except the rice is quite a small portion.

Manager was quick to pull us in with their nett prices and set bundle prices. Menu looks extensive with classic korean dishes. The bulgogi beef rice dish turned out to be minced beef in western tomato like sauce. Duck balls were overcooked and hard. Chicken wings with special sauce turned out soggy and sauce tasted unlike what you would expect. Overall dishes didnt taste authentic korean. First time trying and thoroughly disappointed.
Bad queue system. Lousy service. Side dishes taste much better than main course. Expensive food but bad quality of food and service. Prefer to having meal at big fish.
Ordered some fried chicken. Was expecting a proper, good, deep fried chicken. What I got looks like one from a tze char stall. A bit of flavour, skin is tough, totally meh.
Good, affordable korean food and friendly staff!
Had sweet & spicy chicken wings, seafood kimchi carbonara and beef bulgogi rice, food is up to standard, service was very good too~

Ordered Spicy Bulgogi Rice, grilled chicken cutlet, 2pc SG chicken rice, fried enoki, chicken spam, calamansi juice and rootbeer float. All doesnt taste as good as we hoped for. So disappointing. Never eating here again and would never recommend.

The food is tasty! The manager recommended that I try the kimchi carbonara. Good recommendation...I totally enjoyed my food! Price was reasonable and portion was generous too. Nice ambience to sit under the stars on A cooling evening it s SsoulGood!
So yummy.
Good food and wide selection of flavoured soju. Friendly boss who always make sure that we are enjoying the food. The shop has frequent promotions too!
Take away delivery from   Panda.. Feeling Seoul Good, food is delicious, well packed and well prepared.
Nice environment & food. Friendly staff
nice chicken wing with sweet&spicy sauce
Taste Seoul bad. Expensive too.
The picture on the menu and the actual product differs greatly. Check out the fruit-flavoured bingsus. Also too hard-sell.
Their Special Fried Chicken Wings isnt double Fried like any other Korean Fried Chicken Wings, it is Wet and Soggy with sauce! Bland taste too! Dont bother to Order.
Friendly and good service staff, good food recommendation by staff, stew was very good also.
